        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 4:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Florence, or 27 miles west of Pueblo, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beulah and Wetmore.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
